  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President allowed Vasantha to be detained and investigated",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police Media Spokesperson Senior Superintendent of Police Advocate Nihal Talduwa said that President Ranil Wickremesinghe as Defense Minister has authorized the detention and interrogation of Vasantha Mudalike, Hasantha Gunathilak and Kalwala Sirithamma Thera under the Anti-Terrorism Act for 90 days.",
        "On the 18th, 19 people including Vasantha Mudalike were arrested by the police and 15 of them were recently released on bail during the demonstration held by the student union in Colombo.",
        "According to this, the three including Vasantha Mudalike will be remanded for 72 hours and subject to the permission of the Defense Minister, they will be interrogated for 90 days."
      ],
